  "body": "https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/openstack/openstack.go#L181 checks the instance id via reading the file `/var/lib/cloud/data/instance-id` which is generated by cloud-init, if this lookup fails, the metadata server is connected.\n\nHowever in some cases, the metadata server is not always able to access, and since we write such code to read the instance-id, maybe it would make more sense to mount this file into the pods which are using openstack cloud provider.\n\nI propose to add the condition check to mount this file into these manifests: `kube-apiserver`, `kube-controller-manager` or so.. what do you guys think?\n",
